qas.question: With what accent did Tito speak German according to a biographer?
How much English did Tito speak?
Other than Serbo-Croatian, German, Russian, Czech, Slovenian and English, French and Italian, what language does Tito speak?

context: As regards knowledge of languages, Tito replied that he spoke Serbo-Croatian, German, Russian, and <a1_0>some<a1_0/> English. A biographer also stated that he spoke "Serbo-Croatian ... Russian, Czech, Slovenian ... German (with a <a0_0>Viennese<a0_0/> accent) ... understands and reads French and Italian ... [and] also speaks <a2_0>Kirghiz<a2_0/>."
